4 Config generator
******************

Production installs use the static template
‘/usr/share/doc/casmgr-server/config.json.template’ copied to
‘/etc/casmgr/config.json’.  For development and custom deployments,
generate a config with the *casmgr-config* CLI:

     python -m code_analysis.cli.config_cli generate --help
     python -m code_analysis.cli.config_cli validate --file config.json
     python -m code_analysis.cli.config_cli schema --file config.json

   Installed package:

     /usr/lib/casmgr-server/.venv/bin/python -m code_analysis.cli.config_cli generate ...

Architecture
============

Generation runs in two phases:

  1. ‘SimpleConfigGenerator’ (from ‘mcp-proxy-adapter’) writes ‘server’,
     ‘client’, ‘registration’, ‘auth’, and ‘queue_manager’.
  2. ‘CodeAnalysisConfigGenerator’ reloads the file, adds
     ‘code_analysis’ (database driver, workers, ‘docs_indexing’,
     ‘search_session’), aligns HTTPS protocol fields, applies queue CLI
     overrides, backs up an existing output file to ‘old_code/’, and
     saves JSON.

   The ‘generate’ command always runs ‘CodeAnalysisConfigValidator’
afterward.

Defaults and conventions
========================

MCP port
     *15000* when ‘--server-port’ is omitted (‘code_analysis.port’
     matches).  Production template uses *15010*.
Database driver
     ‘sqlite_proxy’ unless ‘--code-analysis-driver-type postgres’.
Registration
     Requires ‘--with-proxy’.  ‘registration.protocol’ defaults to
     ‘server.protocol’.  ‘registration.server_id’ defaults to
     ‘code-analysis-server’; use ‘code-analysis-server-dev’ on dev hosts
     sharing a proxy with production.
SSL paths
     Stored as absolute paths when the source file exists under the
     current directory.  Validator resolves relative paths against the
     *config file directory*—prefer ‘--out config.json’ at the project
     root or absolute paths.
‘docs_indexing’
     Disabled by default (safe Markdown/JSON/YAML globs under ‘docs/’
     when enabled).
‘search_session’
     Emits ‘ttl_seconds’ and ‘max_block_size_bytes’ from code constants.

Example: dev HTTPS, proxy, PostgreSQL
=====================================

From the git checkout root:

     python -m code_analysis.cli.config_cli generate \
       --protocol https \
       --with-proxy \
       --registration-port 3004 \
       --registration-server-id code-analysis-server-dev \
       --server-port 15000 \
       --server-cert-file mtls_certificates/mtls_certificates/server/code-analysis-server.crt \
       --server-key-file mtls_certificates/mtls_certificates/server/code-analysis-server.key \
       --server-ca-cert-file mtls_certificates/mtls_certificates/ca/ca.crt \
       --registration-cert-file mtls_certificates/mtls_certificates/client/code-analysis.crt \
       --registration-key-file mtls_certificates/mtls_certificates/client/code-analysis.key \
       --registration-ca-cert-file mtls_certificates/mtls_certificates/ca/ca.crt \
       --code-analysis-driver-type postgres \
       --code-analysis-pg-user code_analysis \
       --out config.json

Subcommands
===========

‘generate’ (‘gen’)
     Write config; validate result.
‘validate’ (‘val’)
     ‘--file PATH’ — check config only.
‘schema’
     Apply SQLite schema from config; stops server unless ‘--no-stop’.

   See ‘man casmgr-config’ for the full option list.


