9 PostgreSQL container
**********************

‘casmgr-postgres-container recreate’ removes any old container and
creates a new one:

     sudo casmgr-postgres-container pull
     sudo casmgr-postgres-container recreate
     sudo casmgr-pg-init

   Bind mounts:

Host ‘/var/casmgr/postgres/data’
     Container ‘/var/lib/postgresql/data’
Host ‘/var/casmgr/postgres/cache’
     Container ‘/var/lib/postgresql/cache’
Host ‘/var/log/casmgr/postgres’
     Container ‘/var/log/postgresql’
Host ‘/etc/casmgr’
     Container ‘/etc/casmgr’ (read-only)
Host ‘/etc/casmgr/postgres’
     Container ‘/etc/casmgr/postgres’ (read-only)

   Port publishing: ‘127.0.0.1:5432’ on the host (configurable via
‘code_analysis.database.driver.config.port’).


