13 Upgrade and removal
**********************

*Upgrade:* installing a newer ‘.deb’ pulls the new pinned image, removes
the old container, creates a new one, and re-runs initialization
helpers.  Data in ‘/var/casmgr/postgres/data’ is preserved.  Conffiles
‘/etc/casmgr/config.json’ and ‘/var/casmgr/secrets/.env’ are kept.

   *Remove:* ‘apt remove casmgr-server’ stops services and removes the
container.

   *Purge:* ‘apt purge casmgr-server’ also runs ‘docker rmi’ on the
pinned image.  ‘/var/casmgr’ data is retained unless deleted manually.

   Replaces legacy package ‘code-analysis-server’; disables
‘code-analysis-server.service’ if present.


